Clinical utility


Focus on the quality of decisions driven by dynamic predictions
Based on a clinically relevant decision threshold \(c\in(0,1)\)
\(c\) \(\longrightarrow\) cost of false positives; \(1-c\) \(\longrightarrow\) cost of false negatives







The most used clinical utility metric is the net benefit (NB)
We define the dynamic NB \[ \normalsize\require{color}\begin{split}
    \text{NB}_c\big(\pi_i(s\mid t),& D_i(t,s)\big)  =  \mathbf{1}\{\pi_i(s\mid t)\geq c\} D_i(t,s)\\
    &-\mathbf{1}\{\pi_i(s\mid t)\geq c\}(1- D_i(t,s))\frac{c}{1-c}
\end{split} \]




